guangzhou is the  capital  and the  subprovincial city  of  guangdong   province  in the  southern  part of the  peoples republic of china   the city is also known by an older englishlanguage name canton it is a port on the  pearl river   navigable  to the  south china sea  and is located about 120 km 75 miles northwest of  hong kong  as of the  2000  census the city has a population of 6 million and a metropolitan population of roughly 85 million though some estimates are as high as 126 million   making it the most populous city in the province and the  third most populous   metropolitan area  in mainland  china  the official estimate of the citys population at end 2006 by the provincial government was 9754600
